  "elements": {
    "inscriptions": [
      {
        "id": "insc-1",
        "text": "The Lauderdale Lakes Country Club golf course owes it&apos;s existance to the",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 11
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": -3,
          "y_mm": 363
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-2",
        "text": "tenacity of numerous area residents who stepped in to save it from",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 11
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 340
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-3",
        "text": "development during its 100-plus year history. The course was created in",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 11
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 317
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-4",
        "text": "1921 to use by guests of the nearby Sterlingworth Hotel. In 1936, Lakes",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 11
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 294
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-5",
        "text": "resident Edwin Hawks Ravenscroft bought and redesigned the course, which",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 11
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 271
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-6",
        "text": "he had to shutter during World War II.",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 12
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 248
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-7",
        "text": "At the end of the war, another resident, Waldemar Petersen, formed a group",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 11
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": -1,
          "y_mm": 183
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-8",
        "text": "to buy the course from Ravenscroft and manage it. The group included:",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 12
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 160
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-9",
        "text": "Chuck Morton, as secretary; Harold Leasley, as president; Petersen, as",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 12
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 137
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-10",
        "text": "treasurer; and Phil May, Harold  Mattes, Harold schmid, Harold Pittman, Kirk",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 11
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 114
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-12",
        "text": "shareholders. The group bought the course in December 1945, with",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 12
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 68
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-13",
        "text": "Morton acting as volunteer manager.",
        "font": {
          "family": "Arial",
          "size_mm": 12
        },
        "position": {
          "x_mm": 0,
          "y_mm": 45
        },
        "rotation": {
          "z_deg": 0
        },
        "color": "#ffb35a",
        "surface": "headstone/front"
      },
      {
        "id": "insc-14",
        "text": "In 1973, after expanding the clubhouse, the group sold the course back",
